  <title>quaternary ammonium compounds</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Derivatives of ammonium compounds, (NH4+)Y−, in which all four of the hydrogens bonded to nitrogen have been replaced with hydrocarbyl groups. Compounds having a carbon-nitrogen double bond (i.e. R2C=N+R2Y−) are more accurately called iminium compounds. e.g. [(CH3)4N]+OH−, tetramethylammonium hydroxide.</text>
